This paper discusses privacy risks associated with location metadata, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also presents a tool for evaluating privacy loss caused by location metadata, which involves techniques related to data mining and machine learning (cs.SI). The exploration of automated private information inference involves analyzing large amounts of data, which is related to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the implications of user behavior and preferences, which is related to the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for offering the tool as an auditing tool for major services, which is related to the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
